result.execSummary:
The defendant Lisa M Anderson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property >$2500-$5000 [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime, Penalty - Theft >$2500-$5000], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Consecutive to: Probation is consecutive to the defendant's current prison sentence.

miscConds.notes:
Pay restitution in the amount of $1,350.00 and restitution surcharge. Restitution is joint and several with co-actors, Brian Anderson and Christine Sharp, and is subject to the Defendant's right to challenge.
---------------------------------

Pay court costs and Department of Corrections Supervision Fees.  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment may be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.
---------------------------------

No alcohol.  No illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia. No contact with the victim without the victim's and Agent's consent. No contact with co-defendants, Brian Anderson and Christine Sharp without Agent's permission.
---------------------------------

Counseling as recommended by Probation Agent.  Provide biological specimen to state crime lab for DNA analysis, and pay DNA analysis surcharge.
---------------------------------
AODA assessment and follow through with recommendations.

timeConds.notes: The defendant is to complete a total of one-hundred (100) hours of community service work during her period of probation with NO BUYOUT.

9:32am Court in session

Defendant Lisa M Anderson in court with attorney Ashley L Renz.  Matthew R. Leusink appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
Agent Lisa Lottig appeared. Deft still owes restitution. Atty Renz makes record that Deft was under the impression that the restitution was already paid by a co-actor. Atty Renz requests that the money owed be converted to civil judgment, Deft is working but is not able to pay the full amount owed at this time. ADA Leusink makes record that Deft did not have to pay restitution to one of the victims due to that victim not filing their request timely & the State requests Deft's probation be extended by a year. Response by Agent Lottig to Court's questions. Response by Atty Renz as to Deft's good faith effort. 
Court extends probation for one year, if Deft pays off restitution owed prior to that one year the Court will consider another review hearing.  Defense is requesting the Court reconsider, the co-actors have had civil judgment entered on their cases & she is requesting the Court enter civil judgment for her as well. Response by ADA Leusink as to the status of the co-actors case. Response by Agent Lottig, Deft has not paid anything to date. Atty Renz makes record that Deft is able to pay $150 today. Court makes record once restitution is paid, probation will be terminated. Court extends probation for one year & will terminate upon restitution being paid off. Remaining court costs/fines will be converted to civil judgment once restitution is paid in full.

9:43pm Court in recess
